@page "/harness/extension-hardening"

<PageTitle>Harness — extension hardening</PageTitle>

<h1>Extension hardening</h1>

<section>
    <h2>Extension hardening — colliding modules are skipped, the editor survives</h2>
    @* Three editors, each loading a pair of consumer extension modules that collide in a
       different way. In every case the SECOND module must be skipped with a console error
       while the editor stays alive and typeable — the whole point of failing soft. *@
    <LexicalEditor Id="editor-collide-name"
                   CssClass="harness-collide-name"
                   Theme="LexicalTheme.Default">
        <HarnessCollider Variant="name-a" />
        <HarnessCollider Variant="name-b" />
    </LexicalEditor>

    <LexicalEditor Id="editor-collide-nodetype"
                   CssClass="harness-collide-nodetype"
                   Theme="LexicalTheme.Default">
        <HarnessCollider Variant="node-a" />
        <HarnessCollider Variant="node-b" />
    </LexicalEditor>

    <LexicalEditor Id="editor-collide-declared"
                   CssClass="harness-collide-declared"
                   Theme="LexicalTheme.Default">
        <HarnessCollider Variant="conflict-a" />
        <HarnessCollider Variant="conflict-b" />
    </LexicalEditor>
</section>
